# Development dependencies — human-edited source of truth.
#
# These are layered on top of the runtime lock: `pip-compile` uses
# requirements.lock as a *constraints* file so dev and prod can never
# disagree on a shared dependency's version.
#
# Edit + `make lock` to regenerate requirements-dev.lock.

-c requirements.lock

